ision at the battle of jonesboro brigadier general john c carter was mortally wounded during the battle of franklin on november   and died december  in the harrison home  miles  km south of the battlefield aftermathedit brigadier general john c carter was buried at rose hill cemetery columbia tennessee see alsoedit list of american civil war generals confederate american civil war portal biography portal referencesedit eicher john h and david j eicher civil war high commands stanford stanford university press  isbn  sifakis stewart who was who in the civil war new york facts on file  isbn  warner ezra j generals in gray lives of the confederate commanders baton rouge louisiana state university press  isbn  external linksedit john c carter at find a grave this biographical article related to the united states military is a stub you can help wikipedia by expanding it v t e this article about a person of the american civil war is a stub you can help wikipedia by expanding it v t e retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlejohnccarteroldid categories  births deathspeople from waynesboro georgiauniversity of tennessee alumniconfederate states army generalsconfederate states military personnel killed in the american civil warunited states military personnel stubsamerican civil war biography stubshidden categories articles lacking sources from october all articles lacking sourcesfind a grave template with id same as wikidataall stub articles navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store interaction helpabout wikipediacommunity portalrecent changescontact page tools what links hererelated changesupload filespecial pagespermanent linkpage informationwikidata itemcite this page printexport create a bookdownload as pdfprintable version languages deutsch edit